		<td valign="top">
		<h2><span style="font-weight: 400"><font face="Arial">American Sign Language:&nbsp; 
		</font></span></h2>
		<blockquote>
    <div style="border-style: solid; border-width: 1px; padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px">
		<blockquote>
			<p><font size="4">ASL University is a free resource for 
	American Sign Language students, instructors, interpreters, and parents of 
			Deaf children.&nbsp; It started back in 1997 as an online ASL class 
			offered through the America Online Campus using a chat room and a 
			small website with a few dozen pages. Teachers are welcome to use 
			this curriculum to teach their own in-person ASL courses.</font></blockquote>
	</div>
	<p>
	<font size="4">Hello ASL Scholars!!! </font><font size="5">
	<br>
	</font><font size="4">This site is under <i>constant</i> 
	development. It is not perfect, but it is always (I hope) getting better.<br>
	Signs and information are added almost everyday. <br>
	Cordially,<br>
	-
	Dr. Bill Vicars&nbsp; :) </font><hr color="#000000" size="6" style="border-style: ridge; border-width: 2; padding-left: 0; padding-right: 0; padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0" width="88" align="left">
